            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[# Paper Annotator 1.0.0

The first standalone macOS release of Paper Annotator.

- Open Markdown Manuscripts or paired HTML Previews from Finder, the File menu, drag-and-drop, or Recent Files.
- Read in journal or plain-Markdown views while preserving source-offset Anchors.
- Create, route, review, and human-accept Candidates without writing the Manuscript.
- Run fully offline with the Node engine, Source Han Serif font, and review workbench bundled inside the app.
- Install from a signed, notarized drag-and-drop DMG.
- Receive future signed updates through the public Sparkle channel; installation remains user-controlled.

Requirements: Apple silicon Mac running macOS 10.13 or later.
]]></description>
